CommonFields.Title: Non-covalently modified graphene sheets by imidazolium ionic liquids for multifunctional polymer nanocomposites
Author: Yang, Ying-Kui
He, Cheng-En
Peng, Ren-Gui
Baji, Avinash
Du, Xu-Sheng
Huang, Yuan-Li
Xie, Xiao-Lin
Mai, Yiu-Wing

ChooseParameter.Other:
PMMA was purified by filtering over alumina powder to remove
          the inhibitors before use.

Mixing.Description:
100g of graphite powder and 50g of sodium nitrate was
            stirred into 2.3L of sulfuric acid

60g of potassium permanganate was added while the
            solution was agitated

Solution removed from ice bath, stirred at 35
            Celsius, and then distilled water was added

2.8L of water and 50mL hydrogen peroxide slowly added
            into the solution

ChooseParameter.Other:
The mixture was filtered and washed with 1:10 HCl solution
          (5L) in order to remove metal ions

Mixing.Description:
The as-synthesized GO (300 mg) was ultrasonically
            dispersed in 200 mL aqueous NaOH solution to obtain a yellowbrown
            colloidal suspension.

1.2 g NaBH4 and 100 mL Imi-IL solution in DMSO (10
            mg/mL) were then added to the GO suspension with vigorous
            stirring.

ChooseParameter.Other:
The final product was subsequently subjected to several
          cycles of filtration and washing with water and acetone to remove
          the residual Imi-ILs and other impurities.

Drying-Evaporation.Description:
The Imi-IL functionalized graphene (ImiG) was
            obtained by drying in vacuum.

Mixing.Description:
ImiG sheets were readily dispersed and exfoliated in
          DMF (2 mg/mL) by sonication in a bath at room
          temperature.

An appropriate amount of MMA monomer with 0.5 wt.% AIBN
          was added to the ImiG dispersion by magnetic stirring and the
          mixture was deoxygenated by vacuum/dry nitrogen for several cycles
          in a water–ice bath.

The flask, charged with the above reactants, was placed
          in a preheated oil bath at 70°C to perform free radical
          polymerization under a nitrogen atmosphere and constant
          stirring.

Cooling.Description:
After a 12 h period, the black solution was poured into
          ice-cold methanol to produce a grey-black precipitate.

Drying-Evaporation.Description:
The graphene was obtained by filtration and drying
          overnight at 70°C.

XRay_Diffraction_and_Scattering.Description:
X-ray diffraction experiments were conducted in a
      D/MAX-IIIC X-ray diffractometer with Cu K-alpha radiation.

XRay_Photoelectron_Spectroscopy.Description:
X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy was performed using a
      monochromatic Al K-alpha X-ray source.

Atomic_Force_Microscopy.Equipment:
Digital Instrument Nanoscope IIIA Atomic Force
      Microscope

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description:
Thermal gravimetric analysis was conducted using a TGA-7
      Perkin Elmer calorimeter under argon flow (20 mL/min) at a heating rate
      of 20°C/min.

Electrometry.Description:
DC conductivities were measured by a standard fourprobe
      method using a Keithley 4200 electrometer at room
      temperature.
